{{wikipedia|Watergate scandal}}
==English==
===Etymology===
from the name of the Watergate Hotel
===Pronunciation===
IPA (''US''):  /ˈwɑtərˌgeɪt/
===Proper noun===
'''Watergate'''
# an American [[political]] [[scandal]] (beginning with a [[burglary]] in the Watergate Hotel in Washington in 1972) that eventually led to [[resignation]] of President Richard Nixon
# any scandal usually involving: ''a)'' the abuse of one's [[occupational position]] (especially a [[public]] position, and very especially a significant [[elect|elected]] public position '''or''' high [[appoint|appointed]] public position); ''b)'' [[underhanded]] behavior; and ''c)'' a [[cover-up]]
# [[Watergate salad]]
